         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>288</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979d"/><citedRange>151</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... In a short time certainly (he will (?) ...) together with our sons ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>23</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Thereupon) the 500 sons of the ministers (were ready (?) to go into the forest (?) together with) the Bodhisattva ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having come to the prince, he says: You shall have permission, oh prince. Leave (the house!) ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">You will have permission, prince. Leave the house!</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>226</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... This you will certainly achieve. I did (not) have (the possibility), the distinctiveness, to see ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">You will attain it for sure.  (cf 23)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>625</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>161, 34</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>187</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... When you, led to death by the Caṇḍālas, went into the city, first of all you spoke the word[s] ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>224, 240</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>130</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... for (what) reason have you spoken this talk, which all beings here have heard? ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... through the ... (?) of the world. 1. When he had heard this, the Bodhisattva (, surrounded with rays) a fathom [broad] (, says:) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>16</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... with the energy of a Bodhisattva, with a cheerful mind, with hands folded, to the king: </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>207</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>33</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>105</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... when you gave me into the hands of the executioners [and] ordered them to kill, (I saw (?) the people of the city) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>241</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>37</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... of/to the king. The land is under the protection of the king. The land under the protection ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Das Land befindet sich unter dem Schutz des Königs.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The land is under the protection of the king.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>109</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>159, 164</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>188</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... was there no one in this town, who asked: [Is] my death justified? 1. See, (oh lord) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>188</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... thereby I have found myself tied and (delivered) to the executioners ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">The translation is largely based on <bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>23-24</citedRange></bibl>, and <bibl><title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">This text continues from <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a74"/> and continues on <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a64"/>.</note><note corresp="#a6" type="philcomment">This line seems to be in a tune of 4x12 syllables, rhythm 4/4/4.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">This line is in a tune of 4x14 syllables, rhythm 7/7.</note></p>
